fields.title: Jamaicaâ€™s first Olympic skier
fields.content: Benjamin Alexander is born in the UK in 1983. He has a Jamaican father and in finance. Then, he becomes a DJ. He is very successful in his job. Alexander starts skiing six years ago. He can ski well. This month, he qualifies for the Olympic Games in Beijing, China. This means that he is fast enough to ski with the best skiers in the world. He is not the best. He is on the 4722nd place in the world. He is happy that he can go to the Olympics.

fields.title: Man gives food to dogs
fields.content: A man from Jordan loves animals a lot. He helps street dogs. He gives them food every day. Morshed spends around 1,400 dollars on food for dogs every month. He buys meat. He vaccinates the dogs. It helps them stay healthy.There are many street dogs in Jordan. They are often sick. Most people do not like these dogs. Morshed starts to feed the dogs seven years ago. He makes videos of them. He puts the videos on Tik Tok. Morshed wants to show that dogs are very friendly animals. Morshed believes that people will change their opinion about the dogs. Maybe other people will give food to them, too.
